[[File:EmboProbeDroid-AnOldFriend.png|thumb|right|150px|A small model of probe droid]]
A '''probe droid''', also known as a '''recon droid''', '''probot''', or '''Sensor Droid''', was a type of [[droid]] that could be used for deep space exploration and reconnaissance. They were tenacious hunters and searchers and used manipulator arms to perform various tasks. Notable models included the [[DRK-1 Dark Eye probe droid]] and the [[Viper probe droid]]. They could be equipped with both [[Deflector shield|shields]] and [[blaster]]s.

==History==
[[File:Probe_Droid_SWB.png|thumb|left|125px|An Imperial probe droid]]
The [[Sith Lord]] [[Maul|Darth Maul]] employed three DRK-1 Dark Eye probe droids to search for the [[Jedi]] [[Qui-Gon Jinn]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] on the [[planet]] [[Tatooine]].<ref name="Episode I">{{Film|I}}</ref>

During the [[Clone Wars]], the [[Kyuzo]] [[bounty hunter]] [[Embo]] used a single-[[eye]]d probe droid to track [[Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala]].<ref name="An Old Friend">{{TCW|An Old Friend}}</ref>

The [[Grysk]] operative "[[Jixtus]]" dispatched several probes to the [[planet]] [[Rapacc]] to locate [[The Magys]].<ref name="Lesser Evil">''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Lesser Evil]]''</ref>

To locate the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance's]] secret base after they [[Evacuation of Yavin 4|evacuated]] from [[Yavin 4]], the [[Galactic Empire]] began [[Project Swarm]], which saw probes sent out to find the hidden base.<ref name="Aphra 37">[[Doctor Aphra (2016) 37|''Doctor Aphra'' (2016) 37]]</ref> Eventually, [[XJ9-CS14]], a Viper model having arrived on the planet [[Hoth]] from its [[Avenger|carrier]], began to transmit a live feed of what appeared to be a [[power generator]] to the Empire, leading to an [[Battle of Hoth|attack]] on [[Echo Base]] a short time later. The droid, however, was spotted by [[Han Solo]] prior to the invasion, warning the Alliance and giving them some time to prepare the evacuation.<ref name="Episode V" />

Probe droids were produced for the [[New Republic]] on the planets [[Metalorn]] and [[Troithe]].<ref name="Victory's Price">''[[Victory's Price: An Alphabet Squadron Novel]]''</ref> The [[mercenary]] [[Shin Hati]] used a [[Shin Hati's probe droid|probe droid]] to locate [[Sabine Wren]].<ref name="Part One">{{Ahsoka|Part One: Master and Apprentice}}</ref>

